Reasoning: The paper deals with compressed sensing and sparse recovery, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of nonconvex optimization techniques and the study of the null space of the measurement matrix suggest a numerical analysis (cs.NA) perspective. The topological viewpoint and the study of sets of measure zero and first category suggest a topology (cs.SI) perspective. Finally, the comparison of different cost functions suggests a data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) perspective.
